---
const trustSignals = [
  "approval_request for risky actions",
  "authorization_record for decisions",
  "audit_record for traceable changes",
  "recovery_point before high-impact execution",
  "JSON-RPC boundary between UI and local harness",
  "no direct website dependency on desktop runtime",
];
---

<section id="safety" class="section-frame px-4 py-20 lg:px-0 lg:py-24">
  <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_minmax(0,0.9fr)]">
    <div class="glass-card rounded-[2rem] p-7 lg:p-8">
      <p class="text-sm tracking-[0.28em] text-cc-peach uppercase">Safety and local-first</p>
      <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-4xl font-semibold text-white">A cute interface still needs a serious governance story.</h2>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-8 text-white/72">
        CialloClaw should never be described as magic auto-execution. The project architecture is intentionally built around authorization, audit, recovery, and formal result delivery.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-3">
        {trustSignals.map((signal) => (
          <div class="rounded-[1.35rem] border border-white/10 bg-white/6 px-4 py-4 text-sm leading-7 text-white/72">{signal}</div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="glass-card rounded-[2rem] p-7 lg:p-8">
      <p class="text-sm tracking-[0.28em] text-cc-cyan uppercase">Desktop control surfaces</p>
      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4">
        <article class="rounded-[1.5rem] border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/52 p-5">
          <p class="text-xs tracking-[0.24em] text-white/56 uppercase">Dashboard</p>
          <h3 class="mt-3 font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-white">See the current task, trust summary, and artifact path.</h3>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-white/68">The dashboard is not a feature menu. It is the place to understand what the Agent is doing, where the task is blocked, and whether action is needed from you.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-[1.5rem] border border-white/10 bg-slate-950/52 p-5">
          <p class="text-xs tracking-[0.24em] text-white/56 uppercase">Control panel</p>
          <h3 class="mt-3 font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Tune provider, memory, automation, and safety boundaries.</h3>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-white/68">Model credentials, budget fallback, memory retention, floating ball behavior, and safety expectations all belong in the dedicated settings surface.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
